on that day ten years ago , when this teacher was taking a nap at home during noontime break , the telephone rang suddenly .
she picked up the phone and listened , yet out came a strange rough voice : " we have caught your kid stealing a book. come here quick ! "
coming from the other end of the line was a little girl 's crying  along with loud scolding voices of others .
glancing over at her only daughter , who was watching tv nearby , it suddenly dawned upon her .
obviously , a little girl must have got caught by the sales person while she was stealing a book. as she did not want to let her family know it , she must have made up a phone number at random. that was how they happened to call here .
of course she could put down the phone and ignored the call. she could also even reprimand the other party ,
because this incident had nothing to do with her .
however , being a teacher , she thought she might be her own student .
the phone call gave her some rough idea that the little girl , who made the momentary slip , must be very much frightened and was facing perhaps the most horrifying situation in her life .
hesitating for a moment , an idea suddenly occurred to her. right , just do it this way .
so , after making sure about the bookstore 's address , she hurried there .
just as she expected , a tearful little girl was standing in the bookstore ,
while adults nearby were yelling at her in fierce reproof .
she rushed up to hold the poor little girl in her arms. turning around , she said to the sales person nearby : " talk to me. don 't scare the kid . "
amid the sales person 's reluctant mutterings , she paid the fine of about a few dozen yuan before she was able to lead this little girl out of the bookstore and take a close look at that tear-smudged , terrified face .
she laughed and took the little girl home. she gave her a good cleaning and let the girl go without asking anything .
before she took off , she made a special effort to tell her repeatedly , if you want to read books , just come to the auntie 's place. there are many books inside .
the little girl , who had still not yet recovered from her horror , took a close look at her and scampered away. she never reappeared .
time went by like a rushing stream. ten years had passed in a flash before she knew it .
having long forgotten this thing , she still lived here , leading a quiet and peaceful life .
one day at noon , there was a series of knocks on the door .
when she opened the door , she saw a stranger , a pretty young girl with all smiles on her face and her hands full of gifts .
" who are you looking for ? "
she asked doubtfully .
in her excitement , that girl said a great deal .
only with great efforts in following the narration of that girl , a stranger to her , did she suddenly realize that she was that little girl of that year. she had graduated smoothly from college after ten years and now took this trip purposely to visit her .
with her eyes glistening with tears , the young girl said softly : " though i have never understood even today why you were willing to pretend to be my mom to help me out , i have always felt all these ten years that i want to call you mom . "
the teacher 's eyes also grew blurry .
she asked curiously : " if i had not helped you , what would have happened ? "
the girl 's face immediately darkened. she gently shook her head and said : " i am not sure. i could have done something foolish and might have even committed suicide . "
the teacher 's heart trembled , and she started to feel rejoiced secretly .
the decision she made on the spur of the moment that year turned out to have had such an impact on one person 's life .
looking at the happy smile on the girl 's face , she also smiled .
