the result of this sole successful peasant uprising over 2,000 years turned the chinese people into subhuman beings for a period of time .
now let 's take a look at the middle ages in western europe , known as the dark ages .
the middle ages in western europe was a period of one thousand years which came about after western rome was destroyed by nomads and had nothing to do with the previous ancient greece and rome .
this period was characterized by fiefdoms , namely land fiefdoms .
landlords at lower levels had more independent power .
whether they were small feudal lords with territories extending a few kilometers or the nobility of dukes , marquises , counts , viscounts , and barons who appeared on formal occasions , as people of various ranks were able to mutually check and balance and depend on one another , with the conditions and abilities to fight for their legitimate rights from the king , there were scenes of kings and noblemen sitting together for negotiations of their own respective interests , scenes never seen in ancient chinese history .
they made mutual compromises and concessions instead of overthrowing or superseding other parties by using force .
this way , by means of various kinds of contracts , rights were continuously granted to noblemen and commoners , and with increasing power for noblemen and commoners , the king 's rights became increasingly diminished .
in the end , the british queen became only ceremonial , with no actual power .
democracy was gradually realized through this method !
